'''wrong'''  (''plural:'' '''[[wrongs]]''')

# Something that is [[immoral]] or not good. 
#: ''Injustice is a [[heinous]] '''wrong'''.''
# The [[incorrect]] or [[unjust]] [[position]] or [[opinion]]. (Or is it the wronged?)
#* '''1592''': I [[blame]] not her: she could say little less; She had the '''wrong'''. &mdash; William Shakespeare, ''Henry VI'', Part III, Act IV, Scene I, line 101.
# The [[opposite]] of [[right]]; something which is wrong, particularly [[injustice]].
#* '''1607''': Thus much of this will make [[Black]] [[white]], [[foul]] [[fair]], '''wrong''' [[right]], [[Base]] [[noble]], [[old]] [[young]], [[coward]] [[valiant]]. &mdash; William Shakespeare, ''Timon of Athens'', Act IV, Scene III, line 28.

